{
  "name": "Rebuke Death",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 19th level, when the thaumaturge is reduced to 0 hit points or fewer, the thaumaturge may use two of his remaining invocations to instead be reduced to 1 hit point. Effects that kill the thaumaturge outright without dealing hit point damage are not affected by this ability.</p>\n<h2 id=\"toc19\"><span>Occult Knowledge</span></h2>\n<p>At 2nd level, a thaumaturge gains a +1 bonus to all Knowledge checks, Spellcraft checks, and Use Magic Device checks. This bonus increases by 1 for every 4 additional thaumaturge levels possessed, to a maximum of +5 at 18th level.</p>\n<h2 id=\"toc20\"><span>Bonus Feats</span></h2>\n<p>At 4th level and every 4 levels thereafter, a thaumaturge gains a bonus feat. This may be spent to gain an extra magic talent, or any feat which has casting as a prerequisite (item creation feats, metamagic feats, Sphere Focus, Circle Casting, etc.).</p>\n<h2 id=\"toc21\"><span>Master Invoker</span></h2>\n<p>At 20th level, the thaumaturge selects two invocations other than rebuke death; he may use these invocations at will without using one of his invocations per day.</p>\n",
